@Node "HISTORY" "Stages of program creation."
@{jcenter}
History.
~~~~~~~~
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
version 1.07 @{fg highlight}(28.02.97)@{fg text}@{lindent 11}
-@{lindent 13} Fixed the bug which very seldom caused the "Software failure" message while program finished.
@{lindent 1}
version 1.06 @{fg highlight}(10.02.97)@{fg text}@{lindent 11}
-@{lindent 13} Always while You make import of filetypes into empty list then You received "Not enoght memory" message. This bug is fixed.
Sometimes after "Not enought memory" message the program made same alert message. Fixed.
If one of extracted diz-files is "delete protected", then program stop extract diz-files from all other archives. This bug is fixed.
The full compilation and optimization of sources are made by SAS C version 6.57.
@{lindent 1}
version 1.05 @{fg highlight}(04.10.96)@{fg text}@{lindent 11}
-@{lindent 13} Now the program declines the words. (Read @{" The word declension. " Link "WORD_DECLENSION"}). Maybe it need very little changes in catalogs for some languages.
@{lindent 1}
