@Node "MENU_SRC" "Menu <<Project/Source...>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This menu mean for select directories and files which will be scaned.

   After You select this menu then program let You the system file requester. In dependence of @{" Scan method " Link "MISC_SCAN"}, You will be able select files and/or directories which will be scaned (search in directories is recursive, i.e. program seek archive files not only in these directories but also in all sub-directories, in sub-sub dirs et cetera...).

   Report about select and scan processes is reflected on gadget @{" Source " Link "SRC_FIELD"}.

@EndNode

@Node "MENU_DEST" "Menu <<Project/Destination...>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This menu mean for select file in which will be stored ready list of extracted diz_files.

   After You select this menu then program let You the system file requester for select destination file.

   Report about select process is reflected on gadget @{" Destination " Link "DEST_FIELD"}.

@EndNode

@Node "MENU_PROGRAM" "Menu <<Project/About/Program...>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This menu mean for receive general program information.

   After You select this menu then program report some general information: name, version and purpose of program and also program copyright.

@EndNode

@Node "MENU_AUTHOR" "Menu <<Project/About/Author...>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This menu mean for receive authorship information.

   After You select this menu then program report authorship information and ways for communication.

@EndNode

@Node "MENU_USER" "Menu <<Project/About/User...>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This menu mean for receive information about user.

   After You select this menu if You have @{" personal copy " Link "PERSONAL"} then program report Your own information: user name, firm, city and country. While You do not registration then program report about it and let You possibility for registration.

@EndNode

@Node "MENU_SYSTEM" "Menu <<Project/About/System...>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This menu mean for receive system information.

   After You select this menu then program report some system information: version of Operation System and Workbench, type of processor, co-processor and memory manager unit, size of chip- and fast-memory, and also free memory available.

@EndNode

@Node "MENU_GUIDE" "Menu <<Project/Help guide...>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This menu mean for receive full information about program.

   After You select this menu then program load and open guide file. Language of text is defined with local system settings from up to down in preferable languages list.

@EndNode

@Node "MENU_HIDE" "Menu <<Project/Hide>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This menu transfer program in hidden mode.

   After You select this menu then program close all its windows and in dependence of MUI-preferences put on Workbench screen the app-icon or add own name in Workbench menu "Tools". Double click on app-icon (select menu) wake up the program.

@EndNode

@Node "MENU_QUIT" "Menu <<Project/Quit>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This menu mean for program termination.

   After You select this menu then program stop the work and free occuped memory and resources.

@EndNode

@Node "MENU_EDIT" "Menu <<Settings/Edit...>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This menu mean for come in program parameters selection mode.

   After You select this menu then program open @{"Settings control window" Link "SETS_WIN"}.

@EndNode

@Node "MENU_LOAD" "Menu <<Settings/Load...>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This menu mean for load the program settings.

   After You select this menu then program load permanent settings from disk and in dependence of ones change current settings.

@EndNode

@Node "MENU_SAVE" "Menu <<Settings/Save...>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This menu mean for save the program settings.

   After You select this menu then program save current program settings on disk as permanent settings.

@EndNode

@Node "MENU_MUI_INFO" "Menu <<MUI/About>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This menu mean for receive information about @{" MUI " Link "MUI"}.

@EndNode

@Node "MENU_MUI_PREFS" "Menu <<MUI/Prefs>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This menu mean for edit preferences of @{" MUI " Link "MUI"}.

@EndNode

@Node "SRC_FIELD" "Gadget <<Source>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This gadget mean for select files/directories which will be scaned, and also for receive information about select, scan and sort processes and about results of ones.

   Gadget has two areas - text field for receive some information and button for source selection. Pushing this button is same as menu @{" Source... " Link "MENU_SRC"}.

@EndNode

@Node "DEST_FIELD" "Gadget <<Destination>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This gadget mean for select destination file and for receive information about select and work processes and about results of ones.

   Gadget has two areas - text field for receive some information and button for destination selection. Pushing this button is same as menu @{" Destination... " Link "MENU_DEST"}.

@EndNode

@Node "MAIN_START_BUT" "Button <<Start>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This button mean for run of diz_texts extract process from selected source files and store these texts into destination file.

   This button is disabled as long as there are not selected either source or destination.

@EndNode

@Node "MAIN_QUIT_BUT" "Button <<Quit>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This button mean for same as menu @{" Quit " Link "MENU_QUIT"}.

@EndNode

@Node "SETS_WIN" "Settings control window description."
@{jcenter}
Settings control window.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    Settings control window is main way for program parameters configuration. This window has:

@{apen 2}@{bpen 3}                                   @{b}Pages@{ub}                                  @{bg back}@{fg text}

@{"               FileTypes            " Link "TYPES_PAGE"}  @{"           Miscellaneous           " Link "MISC_PAGE"}

@{apen 2}@{bpen 3}                                  @{b}Buttons@{ub}                                 @{bg back}@{fg text}

  @{"     Save     " Link "SETS_SAVE_BUT"}    @{"     Load     " Link "SETS_LOAD_BUT"}    @{"      Use     " Link "SETS_USE_BUT"}    @{"    Cancel    " Link "SETS_CANCEL_BUT"}

@{b}Note:@{ub} @{i}Please do not forget that all parameters which are edited in this window, are copy of current only. For change current or permanent settings You must use corresponding buttons are placed at the bottom of window. If You close window simply with gadget then all changes will be lost.

@EndNode

@Node "TYPES_PAGE" "FileTypes page."
@{jcenter}
FileTypes page.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    All means of this page are used for filetypes configuration. Filetypes are varieties of archives and files. The page has two areas: left for the list, and right for the editor.

   @{b}List group@{ub} include some features:

@{" List   " Link "SETS_LIST"}
@{i}buttons@{ui}
@{" Up     " Link "LIST_UP_BUT"}
@{" Down   " Link "LIST_DOWN_BUT"}
@{" New    " Link "LIST_NEW_BUT"}
@{" Merge  " Link "LIST_MERGE_BUT"}
@{" Delete " Link "LIST_DELETE_BUT"}

   @{b}Editor area@{ub} has gadgets:

@{" Identification " Link "EDIT_ID"}
@{" Type name      " Link "EDIT_NAME"}
@{" Hex-contents   " Link "EDIT_HEX"}
@{" Suffix         " Link "EDIT_SUFFIX"}
@{" Datatype       " Link "EDIT_DATATYPE"}
@{" Command        " Link "EDIT_COMMAND"}
@EndNode

@Node "SETS_LIST" "List of filetypes."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This window area contains the list of names of all definited filetypes.

   Any name selection with mouse or from keyboard cause to copy all parameters of selected filetype into editor area.

@EndNode

@Node "LIST_UP_BUT" "Button <<Up>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   Pushing this button move up selected filetype in the list.

   If a filetype is used often then place one in the beginning of list.

@EndNode

@Node "LIST_DOWN_BUT" "Button <<Down>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   Pushing this button move down selected filetype in the list.

   If a filetype is used rarely then place one in the end of list.

@EndNode

@Node "LIST_NEW_BUT" "Button <<New>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   Pushing this button reserve the line in list for new filetype.

   New line is added in the end of list. At the same time program activate the editor gadget @{" Type name " Link "EDIT_NAME"} for insert the name of new filetype.

@EndNode

@Node "LIST_MERGE_BUT" "Button <<Merge>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This button mean for import of filetypes.

   If You want for import of filetypes from other user then may use this button. It is not hard. After You push this button then program let You the system file requester. In this requester You must select file which contains import filetypes. After that program add new filetypes to exist ones.

@EndNode

@Node "LIST_DELETE_BUT" "Button <<Delete>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   Pushing this button delete selected filetype in the list.

   This button is disabled as long as there is not selected filetype in the list.

@EndNode

@Node "EDIT_ID" "Gadget <<Identification>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This cycle gadget define way for filetype identification. It is resemble on same which is used in program @{b}DirectoryOpus@{ub}.

   Now, next methods are available:

-@{b}Only hex@{ub}:
File is identify with verify its contents. If initial file contents coincide with contents of gadget @{" Hex-contents " Link "EDIT_HEX"} then this file belong to corresponding filetype.

-@{b}Only suffix@{ub}:
File is identify with verify suffix of its name. If filename suffix coincide with contents of gadget @{" Suffix " Link "EDIT_SUFFIX"} then this file belong to corresponding filetype.

-@{b}hex and suffix@{ub}:
File is identify both with verify its contents and with verify suffix of its name. Only if both examination are pass out, then this file belong to corresponding filetype.

-@{b}hex or suffix@{ub}:
File is identify both with verify its contents and with verify suffix of its name. If even though one examination is pass off, then this file belong to corresponding filetype.

-@{b}Datatype@{ub}:
File is identify with using system datatypes. If file datatype same as indicate in gadget @{" Datatype " Link "EDIT_DATATYPE"}, then this file belong to corresponding filetype.

@EndNode

@Node "EDIT_NAME" "Gadget <<Type name>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This gadget mean for edit filetype name.

@{b}Notes:@{ub}
@{i}Maximal name length - 20 characters.
The filetype name is case-sensitive.@{ui}

@EndNode

@Node "EDIT_HEX" "Gadget <<hex-contents>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This gadget define hex-contents which will be used for filetype identification.

   For easy edit there are two check modes: hex and ASCII. Some special characters and sequences may be used in this gadget. It is:

@{b}$@{ub} -@{lindent 5} if in hex mode then switch to ASCII mode, if in ASCII mode then simply check for character '$';@{lindent 1}
@{b}#@{ub} -@{lindent 5} if in ASCII mode then switch to hex mode (if You is in need to check for character '#' then use combination '##');@{lindent 1}
@{b}?@{ub} -@{lindent 5} if in hex mode then skip one byte, if in ASCII mode then simply check for character '?';@{lindent 1}
@{b}<hex-value>@{ub} -@{lindent 5} if in hex mode then skip indicated number of bytes. Maximal dimension is 255 bytes (hex-value FF). Dimension must be defined as @{b}hexadicemal@{ub} value.
@{lindent 1}
Examples:
For identification of JPG-file: @{b}FFD8FFE0??$JFIF@{ub};
for IFF ILBM: @{b}$FORM#<4>$ILBM@{ub};
for DMS archive: @{b}$DMS!@{ub}.

@{b}Notes:@{ub}
@{i}Maximal line length - 60 characters.
@{i}Maximal dimension for check contents - 256 bytes.
Default check mode is hex.@{ui}

@EndNode

@Node "EDIT_SUFFIX" "Gadget <<Suffix>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This gadget define filename suffix which will be used for filetype identification.

   If a filetype contains some files with different suffixes, then these suffixes must be enumerated through space.

Example:
Program LZX can decompress also LHA and LZH archives (but if You have registered version of LZX only!) and do it faster than LhA. Therefore we may create one filetype for these archives, ex. named @{b}LH_CLONE@{ub} with set @{" Identification " Link "EDIT_ID"} to suffix method and enter in suffix gadget: @{b}lzx lha lzh@{ub}.

@{b}Notes:@{ub}
@{i}Maximal line length - 40 characters.
Line contents is case-insensitive.@{ui}

@EndNode

@Node "EDIT_DATATYPE" "Gadget <<Datatype>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This gadget define datatype name which will be used for filetype identification.

   As rule the name of datatype is same as file which define one. These files are placed in system directory @{b}DEVS:Datatypes@{ub}.

   If a filetype contains some files from different datatypes, then these datatypes must be enumerated through space.

@{b}Notes:@{ub}
@{i}Maximal line length - 40 characters.
Line contents is case-insensitive.@{ui}

@EndNode

@Node "EDIT_COMMAND" "Gadget <<Command>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This gadget define command string which will be used for run of diz_text extractor.

   This is important gadget in filetypes page. The line construction is:

   @{b}PATH_&_NAME_OF_EXTRACTOR PARAMETERS SPECIAL_KEYS@{ub}, where:

- @{b}PATH_&_NAME_OF_EXTRACTOR@{ub}:
Path and/or name of program which will be used for extract of diz_text. You may use assigned names and also one special alias: @{b}PROG_DIR@{ub}. This alias is used for define the path which ListDIZ locate in. If extractor name or its path have spaces then You must use quotation marks for ones. You may not indicate the full extractor path because if You specify only name of extractor or if extractor is not located with indicated path then ListDiz make search for extractor with all paths which are is used by system for default path (ones are defined with CLI-command PATH). Notwithstanding at this autosearch I recommend use full and correct path of extractor still.
Examples:
@{b}Đ:DMS@{ub}
@{b}PROG_DIR:c/extractor@{ub}.
@{b}"MY TOOLS:Dizzy/c/Magic Extractor"@{ub}.

- @{b}PARAMETERS@{ub}:
It is parameters which are used with extractor. There are some special aliases which @{b}must@{ub} be used instead of some parameters. It is:
@{b}SRC_FILE@{ub} - the archive file which will be work up with extractor;
@{b}DEST_FILE@{ub} - the destination file if extractor is in need to define of destination file;
@{b}DEST_DIR@{ub} - the destination directory if extractor is in need to define of destination directory;
@{b}DIZ_FILE@{ub} - alias for filename "File_id.diz".
Example:
@{b}Đ:LhA e SRC_FILE DIZ_FILE DEST_DIR@{ub}

- @{b}SPECIAL_KEYS@{ub}:
There are some keywords for flexible control of extract process and for use program which even has not extract function (!). It is:
@{b}CURRENT_MODE@{ub} - this key must be used if extractor place diz_text only in system current directory;
@{b}VIEW_MODE@{ub} - this key must be used if program has not extract function but has the view diz_text function;
@{b}FAST_METHOD@{ub} - if You have more free memory then use this key. It do program work faster;
@{b}VM_START@{ub} and @{b}VM_END@{ub} - may be used with @{b}VIEW_MODE@{ub}. There is one reason for using these keywords: some programs add own text into output while show diz_text. These keywords were made especially for this case. Key @{b}VM_START@{ub} define text which diz_text place behind. All output text up to text which defined after key @{b}VM_START@{ub} as well as defined text will be cut off. Key @{b}VM_END@{ub} define text which diz_text place before. All output text after text which defined after key @{b}VM_END@{ub} as well as defined text will be cut off. After these keywords must be placed text which is put in quotation marks and is used for limitation. This text may contains as characters as hex-values. For enter hex code use backslash (\\). If You is in need to enter quotation marks or backslash then use combination \\" and \\\\.
Examples:
@{b}Đ:Lzx e SRC_FILE DIZ_FILE DEST_DIR FAST_METHOD@{ub}
@{b}Đ:ARC e SRC_FILE DIZ_FILE CURRENT_MODE@{ub}
@{b}Đ:DMS viewdiz SRC_FILE VIEW_MODE VM_START "Viewing FILE_ID.DIZ Text\\0A" VM_END "\\0A\\9B\\30"@{ub}
I do not recommend to use the last example because program DMS may be used more easy:
@{b}Đ:DMS viewdiz SRC_FILE SAVE DEST_FILE@{ub}.

@{b}Notes:@{ub}
@{i}Attention: New value of maximal line length - 345 characters.
All aliases and keywords must be upper-case.@{ui}

@EndNode

@Node "MISC_PAGE" "Miscellaneous page."
@{jcenter}
Miscellaneous page.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    All means of this page are used for program configuration. This page has three gadgets groups:

@{b}Group "Control"@{ub}
@{" Scan method      " Link "MISC_SCAN"}
@{" Report mode      " Link "MISC_REPORT"}
@{" Sort method      " Link "MISC_SORT"}
@{" Show time        " Link "MISC_TIME"}
@{" List width       " Link "MISC_WIDTH"}
@{" Diz width        " Link "MISC_DWIDTH"}

@{b}Group "Flags"@{ub}
@{" Autostart        " Link "MISC_ASTART"}
@{" Quiet            " Link "MISC_QUIET"}

@{b}Group "DOS"@{ub}
@{" Source path      " Link "MISC_SRC"}
@{" Destination file " Link "MISC_DEST"}

@EndNode

@Node "MISC_SCAN" "Scan method."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This gadget define the way which will be used for select and scan of source.

   Method "@{b}Only files@{ub}" allow to select as source the files only.

   Method "@{b}Recursive@{ub}" allow to select as files as directories. In this case directories will be scaned recursive i.e. program will seek archive files not only in these directories but also in all sub-directories, in sub-sub dirs et cetera...

@EndNode

@Node "MISC_REPORT" "Report mode"
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This gadget define the way which will be used for report to user about course of extract process.

   In mode "@{b}Progress indicator@{ub}" You may watch course of work with special marked indicator. About one read chapter @{" Progress indicator window " Link "INDI_WIN"}.

   Mode "@{b}Diz_text window@{ub}" allow to see every extracted diz_text as long as You defined in gadget @{" Show time " Link "MISC_TIME"}. About one read chapter @{" Diz_text window " Link "SHOW_WIN"}.

   In mode "@{b}Off@{ub}" program do not report about course of extract process.

@EndNode

@Node "MISC_SORT" "Sort method."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This gadget define the way which will be used for the sorting of source files in each selected directory.

   Method "@{b}Name@{ub}" sort files by their names in alphabetical order.
   Method "@{b}Date@{ub}" sort files by dates of last change of them from oldest up to newest.
   Method "@{b}Size@{ub}" sort files by their size from short up to more long.
   Method "@{b}Off@{ub}" switch off the sorting. Files and directories will be scaned by loading sequence.

   If You select the method which different from "Off" then program also sorts the directories. Directories were sorted by their names.

@EndNode

@Node "MISC_TIME" "Show time."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This gadget define the time duration for show of an extracted diz_text in the @{" Diz_text window " Link "SHOW_WIN"}.

   For show of a diz_text it is in need to set gadget @{" Report mode " Link "MISC_REPORT"} to mode "Diz_text window".

   The time indicates in seconds (approximately). There are two special values:

extreme left "@{b}without wait@{ub}" - program will not make delay for show;
extreme right "@{b}ask for continue@{ub}" - diz_text will be showed as long as You do not confirm to continue.
@EndNode

@Node "MISC_WIDTH" "List width."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This gadget define the list lines width.

   It may be good if You look the diz-list by program which has the text width limitaion (ex. More, MuchMore, ppMore or DirectoryOpus 4.xx). As a rule such program transfer text which do not find room for, onto new line. It break text layout and make hard text perception.

   If width of any list line exceed defined in this gadget value then this line will be cut off. In other words: the ready diz-list will not have lines with width more than defined in this gadget.

   The width indicates in characters. There is special value: extreme right "@{b}unlimited@{ub}" - the width of lines is unlimited. (ex. for GoldED, Moor...).

@EndNode


@Node "MISC_DWIDTH" "Diz width."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This gadget define the control width for lines of diz-texts.

   There are some text files (especially with NFO suffix) which have damaged diz-text. These diz-texts have not ended diz-identificator. ( Hey, merry chaps, please stop do it! ). This shortcomming result in extract not only diz-text but also the text placed after diz-text.

   However, the width of diz-text lines more less than one of page, therefore there is possible to cut off superfluous text by control at width of diz-text lines. If width of diz-text line exceed defined in this gadget value then end of diz-text will be fixed and this line & all next lines will be ignored. In other words: the end of diz-text will be detected as by the end-identificator as by the control at width of diz-text lines.

   The width indicates in characters. There is special value: extreme right "@{b}unlimited@{ub}" - the width of diz-text lines is not controled (but I do not recommend use this value).

@EndNode

@Node "MISC_ASTART" "Flag <<Autostart>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This flag on/off the autostart mode.

   If You use the program often & often, if You have special directory which archives place in, and lastly if You is tired of select source, destination and everytime press @{" Start " Link "MAIN_START_BUT"} then use this flag !

   For autostart mode You must set this flag and save settings. Now after You start the program then one scan source directory which defined in gadget @{" Source path " Link "MISC_SRC"} (scan is recursive) and run extract process itself. And some more: if You as big lazy-bones as I then You may set flag @{" Quiet " Link "MISC_QUIET"} in addition.

@EndNode

@Node "MISC_QUIET" "Flag <<Quiet>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This flag on/off the quiet mode.

   This is standard flag for some applications. It allow to ignore program requesters about insignificiant errors and problems and save your time. If You set this flag then You will be able not sit by the monitor in waiting for next program requester.

   If some unimportant error occur then program save error message in destination file and continue its work. Number of errors will be indicated in the report requester after program finished.

   Not all errors may be ignored. For instance the shortage of memory or the impossibility of save to destination file result in stop of extract process and popup the requester.

@EndNode

@Node "MISC_SRC" "Source path."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This gadget define the directory which will be worked up if flag @{" Autostart " Link "MISC_ASTART"} was set, or define default path for requester which is used for gadget @{" Source " Link "MENU_SRC"}.

@EndNode

@Node "MISC_DEST" "Destination file."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This gadget define default destination file for requester which is used for gadget @{" Destination " Link "MENU_DEST"} and destination file for @{" Autostart " Link "MISC_ASTART"} mode.

@EndNode

@Node "SETS_SAVE_BUT" "Button <<Save>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This button mean for save permanent settings.

   After You press this button then all program settings from @{" Settings control window " Link "SETS_WIN"} will be saved on disk as permanent and accepted as current settings.

@EndNode

@Node "SETS_LOAD_BUT" "Button <<Load>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This button mean for load permanent settings from disk.

   This button do not same as menu @{" Settings/Load " Link "MENU_LOAD"}. This button load permanent settings from disk to @{" Settings control window " Link "SETS_WIN"} only, but do not change current settings.

@EndNode

@Node "SETS_USE_BUT" "Button <<Use>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This button mean for change current settings.

   After You press this button then all program settings from @{" Settings control window " Link "SETS_WIN"} will be accepted as current settings.

@EndNode

@Node "SETS_CANCEL_BUT" "Button <<Cancel>>."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This button mean for close window.

   After You press this button then @{" Settings control window " Link "SETS_WIN"} will be closed without change any settings.

@EndNode

@Node "INDI_WIN" "Progress indicator window description."
@{jcenter}
Progress indicator window.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This window mean for report to user about course of extract process.

   Progress indicator window has some areas:

@{b}Filename@{ub} - the name of current working up file;
@{b}special indicator@{ub} - the progress indicator with the gauge strip, the scale and the text about number of files which done and rest.
@{b}button "Stop"@{ub} - the button for terminate of extract process.

@EndNode

@Node "SHOW_WIN" "Diz_text window description."
@{jcenter}
Diz_text window.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This window mean for show to user every extracted diz_text.

   Diz_text window has some areas:

@{b}show area@{ub} - in this field diz_text will be showed;
@{b}button "Continue"@{ub} - the button for confirm to continue;
@{b}button "Stop"@{ub} - the button for terminate of extract process.

@EndNode

@Node "REGI_WIN" "Registration window description."
@{jcenter}
Registration window.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This window mean for create the @{" Personal copy " Link "PERSONAL"} of program.

   Registration window has some gadgets:

@{b}Name@{ub}    - for enter your name (maximal 40 characters);
@{b}Firm@{ub}    - for enter your firm (maximal 40 characters);
@{b}City@{ub}    - for enter your city (maximal 40 characters);
@{b}Country@{ub} - for enter your country (maximal 40 characters);
@{b}Order@{ub}   - for enter your personal registration number;
@{b}button "Okay"@{ub} - the button for (no)registration.
@EndNode

@Node "PERSONAL" "Personal copy."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   Program ListDIZ is not need registration. Even if You have not personal copy then the program and all its functions will work full and completely. But if You wish to see in menu @{" Project/About/User..." Link "MENU_USER"} your own information then register program please. It is @{b}free of charge@{ub}. All what it want - send me file of program settings with your own data.

   Do it like this:
- Select "@{b}About user@{ub}" menu and push button "@{b}Registration@{ub}";
- Fill all gadgets in registration window with the exception "@{b}Order@{ub}";
- Push button "@{b}Okay@{ub}";
- Save settings with menu @{" Settings/Save " Link "MENU_SAVE"};
-@{lindent 3} Send the file "@{b}ListDIZ.prefs@{ub}" to @{" author " Link "ADDRESS"} on 3,5 diskette (880K) (I am sorry, but I have not got a modem yet);@{lindent 1}
-@{lindent 3} Do not forget to indicate the way which I may use for send You personal registration number (modem, post address or tel.) and write me some words about yourself and about program ListDIZ (the criticism, offers, recommendations, bugs report...).@{lindent 1}

@{b}Notes:@{ub}
@{i}-@{lindent 3} If You can not send file in disk then send the letter with data for registration (name, firm etc...) or telephone me (but I am very seldom at home and I speak english worse than write one, sorry).@{lindent 1}
-@{lindent 3} The support of author with not only words is accepted too.@{ui}
@EndNode

