@Node "QUESTIONS" "Questions & answers."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
@{"[O]" Link "PROG_CRASH"} If program do not work...
@{"[O]" Link "MUI_KEYBOARD"} About usage of keyboard...
@{"[O]" Link "REQ_MULTISELECT"} How do select several files/directories ?
@{"[O]" Link "PROG_CREATE"} How was the program created ?
@{"[O]" Link "FAST_N_FASTER"} How make the work more faster ?
@{"[O]" Link "FREEWARE"} How did it happen that ListDiz is FreeWare ?

@EndNode

@Node "PROG_CRASH" "If program do not work..."
@{jright}@{apen 2}Error isn't error but a system function.
@{fg text}@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   There are not programs without errors, but there are programs which can manage with ones and programs which can not do it. Former detect error and try to ward off its result, the latter do not notice one and it may result in anything.

   Program ListDIZ has builtin hightech system for catch of errors. If error occur while program start then process will be aborted and program report You about error. If error occur in process of work (as of rule it is lack of memory or DOS errors) then, different of serious of error, the program terminate current operation or make quit. In both cases the program flush all used buffers and give back to system the allocated memory and resources, and also the program anyhow try to report about problem.

   Thereby the crash of program is unlikely. However, @{b}Amiga@{ub} is real multitasking machine and program ListDIZ use some its features & resources (external libraries, fonts, ports, some other programs etc...). If program ListDIZ is crashed then it may be not itself error but external problems.

@EndNode

@Node "PROG_CREATE" "How was the program created ?"
@{jright}@{apen 2}It is better to tinker with editor into someself code,
than with finger into own ass...
@{fg text}@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   The program was created according as idea of object-oriented programming. The @{" MUI " Link "MUI"} help me very good in it.

   Program ListDIZ was wrote on "C". In writting I use some programs:

@{b}- Complete package SAS/C.@{ub}@{lindent 3} Version 6.56-6.57. Copyright ©1992-1997 SAS Institute Inc., SAS Campus Drive, Cary, NC 27513, USA.@{lindent 1}

@{b}- Text editor GoldEd.@{ub}@{lindent 3} Version 3.1.3-4.2.3. Copyright ©1995-1997 Dietmar Eilert.@{lindent 1}

@{b}- Graphic editor Personal Paint.@{ub}@{lindent 3} Version 6.3-7.0. Copyright ©1992-1997 Cloanto Italia srl & Nomad Publishing Corporation.@{lindent 1}

@{b}- Catalog editor CatEdit.@{ub}@{lindent 3} Version 1.2. Copyright ©1993-1994 Rafael D'Halleweyn.@{lindent 1}

@{b}- Rusifier.@{ub}@{lindent 3} Version 39.8. Copyright ©1994-1996 Dmitry Mikhilov.

@EndNode

@Node "FAST_N_FASTER" "How make the work more faster ?"
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   Very simple way is in buying the Amiga A4000T with processor board on 68060 !!! If You have not in stock the five thousand bucks (or You as author have nothing) then read further.

   In the main the program speed depend on used extractors. Thus if You use DMS archives and change extractor from @{b}DMS@{ub} to @{b}DMSDescript@{ub} then it make the work on 4 (!) times faster.

   There are some factors which have influence on program speed also. I recommend:

-@{lindent 3} place filetypes which are used often in the beginning of filetype list;@{lindent 1}

-@{lindent 3} use as long as possible @{" identification " Link "EDIT_ID"} with suffix. Identification with datatypes take on 9% more time than with suffix;@{lindent 1}

-@{lindent 3} do not use without urgency the @{" repot mode " Link "MISC_REPORT"} "Diz_text window". The mode "Progress indicator" take on 3% and mode "Diz_text window" on 22% more time than mode "Off";@{lindent 1}

-@{lindent 3} if You have more memory then use keyword @{" FAST_METHOD " Link "EDIT_COMMAND"}. It make program speed up on 11%;@{lindent 1}

-@{lindent 3} place destination file on RAM-disk. Even if You use high-speed media then this method save to You about 5% of time. Also it add life of your media and defend data on media against casual errors.

-@{lindent 3} if it is possible then indicate the full extractor path in line @{" Command " Link "EDIT_COMMAND"}. Otherwise ListDiz will make autosearch for extractor but this process take some (may be big) additional time.


@{b}Note:@{ub}
@{i} The program speed not depend on the sorting method.@{ui}

@EndNode

@Node "MUI_KEYBOARD" "About usage of keyboard..."
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   The usage of keyboard in @{" MUI " Link "MUI"} is full described in docs for MUI.

   In short. Press @{b}TAB@{ub} key for gadget selection. For gadget control, in depend of gadget type, use @{b}RETURN@{ub}, @{b}SPACE@{ub}, cursor arrows keys and their combinations with pushed @{b}SHIFT@{ub}.

@EndNode

@Node "REQ_MULTISELECT" "How do select several files/directories ?"
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This is eternal question of begginers.

   Well, several files is selected same as one file - with mouse. But push and hold any @{b}SHIFT@{ub} key.

@EndNode

@Node "FREEWARE" "How did it happen that ListDiz is FreeWare ? "
@{jright}To programmers: @{apen 2}Hackers break programs not in the least
for the diminish of your income but
for the demonstration of your unskilfulness.
@{fg text}@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   In this chapter I apply to colleagues-programmers. Perhaps some of them will not like next words. Okay, we may have own opinion but I say my one.

   So, why did ListDiz is made as FreeWare? There are many programs are made as ShareWare. Everyone of them demands at least one dollar for author otherwise You will have got the castrated version which make nothing except registration requesters.

   Well, I have nothing against reward of authors. But, my dear programmers, I know what is what, including that our conceit outstrip our real faculty often & often. Yes, there are cleverest programmers who besides make the necessary software in the necessary time. And it is a sin if You can recompense for them but do not it.

   Thus I ask all programmers to balance own desire for money and the importance of created program. Often there are "programs" which may be created on the calculator by baby's little toe of left foot, but this shit demands good fee for "hard work" of author. Bless my soul! As Mark Twain said: "Noise proves nothing. Often a hen who has merely laid an egg cackles as if she laid an asteroid." Strictly speaking: why do user pay for ungifted work? Is it for propagation one?

   My friends, the importance of program is conditioned not with its price, but vice versa. And if we speak about self-conceit then acknowledgement from users is obtained by the toil at program, by the need and the quality of one.

   I am not a professional programmer, I write software not for money. That is true, I do not intend to cheat users with label "ShareWare" and with ceiling prices. That is why I write free distributable software. I think that FreeWare is not cheap software but is style of life!
@{jright}Sergeev Oleg.
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
P.S. "Yor can fool some of the people all of the time, and all of the people some of the time, but you cannot fool all of the people all of the time." (Abraham Lincoln). Programmers, please do not forget about it!
@EndNode
